Rice stocks in India are about to set a positive momentum in coming weeks for good investment return as favorable facts are boiling up.  India being the highest export of rice ,with 40% share, rules the pricing momentum in the rice world followed by Thailand with 15%. In coming weeks, i am expecting rice prices to shoot up around the world.  
 
Supporting factors: 
 • Thailand has recommended to plant only ONE crop to farmers on fears of El-NiNo 
 • Food Corporation of India's (FCI) rice stock is at lowest levels in five years. 
 • India's additional 20% duty hasn't  affected world demand and we saw rise of 3% in export.   
 
Resisting Factors: 
 • IMD predicts El-NiNo to have low impact on India and rainfall should be normal. 
 • Government has no plans yet to unlock the ban which means supply in India will remain normal.
